    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n1. Find the `custom.py` file and define a `turn_right()` function.\r\n   - **Hint:** Refer to the `move_fast()` function from the previous level as a guide.\r\n   - *Consider: How do you add a comment about this function, and what should it say?*\r\n2. Run and test your code.\r\n   \r\n   Think about:\r\n   - *Where should you call your `turn_right()` function? Try it!*\r\n   - *Can you call the `move_fast()` and `turn_right()` functions multiple times in sequence? Try it!*\r\n3. **Consider:** How does defining your own function make your code easier to reuse?\r\n4. Save your code to the Backpack! Click below to see how!\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n::: details [**🔎 Show me how**]\r\n![](https://images.code.org/8658ecc23b62e56425b3894ba3ee17c0-image-1741365862125.png)\r\n:::\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n::: details [**Click Here to Learn How To Save your code to the Backpack!**]\r\n\r\n- Click the three-dot menu icon next to the `custom.py` file name.\r\n- Select \"Save to backpack\" from the drop-down menu.\r\n- Click the \"Save to backpack\" button in the pop-up dialog box.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://images.code.org/a5083c7ccc54bfa4ea561fa29adf2902-image-1740077664809.gif\" style=\"width:450px;\">\r\n:::\r\n\r\n",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\nimport custom\n\nluna = Painter()\nluna.take_paint()\n\ncustom.move_fast(luna)\nluna.paint('blue')\ncustom.move_fast(luna)\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        },
        "2": {
          "id": "2",
          "name": "custom.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "# This function makes the Painter move forward 3 squares\ndef move_fast(painter):\n  painter.move()\n  painter.move()\n  painter.move()\n\n# Add turn_right() function definition below\n\n\n\n# Add turn_around() function definition below\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": false,
          "open": true
        }
